title.narrative: 5.4 HEALTH/HIV

description.narrative: UNICEF EAPR has strengthened capacity to design and implement gender responsive, equity focused HEALTH/HIV programmes that deliver results for the most disadvantaged children at scale., which contributes to Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: COs practice programming excellence to achieve quality results for children at scale in both development and humanitarian settings

description.narrative: EAPRO provided technical support towards building resilience of health systems. This included measures to respond to COVID-19, prepare for vaccine rollout/delivery, and ensure the continuance of essential maternal, newborn and child health services. In partnership with the Global Demand Hub, EAPRO developed guidance and job aids to improve public health messaging and strengthen health worker interpersonal communications to address vaccine hesitancy. To cope with the influx of vaccines, digital health technology was leveraged to increase scale and access. Additionally, EAPRO targeted its engagement through South-South/North-South collaboration to support the elimination of mother-to-child transmission of HIV, Syphilis and Hepatitis B. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/03/2022
